      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:15:3",
      "text": [
        " كَانَتْ عَلَى الْمَلَائِكَةِ الْعَمَائِمُ الْبِيضُ الْمُرْسَلَةُ يَوْمَ بَدْرٍ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ibn Fazzal, from Abu Jameela, from Jabir, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘There were white turbans upon the Angels Sent on the Day of Badr’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "3. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from ibn Faddal from abu Jamilah from Jabir who has said the following: “Abu Ja‘far, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that the angels had turbans hanging on them on the day of Badr.” "
        ]
      }
